<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA75">
<l>peruku matavēḻa māppiṭikku muṉṉiṉ</l>
<l>ṟiruka ṇiḷamūṅkil vāṅki – yarukirunta</l>
<l>tēṉkalantu nīṭṭun tiruvēṅ kaṭaṅkaṇṭīr</l>
<l>vāṉkalanta vaṇṇaṉ varai</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>See Tiruvēṅkaṭam,<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For this earlier type of inset clause typical of Caṅkam literature cf. note on Po. 38, with further parallels in Po. 40, Pū. 53, Pē. 45, 58, 68, 71, 72, 75 and 89. This one is based on the well-established Pālai topos of the elephant feeding its hungering cow, showing the aruḷ expected from the god.</note></l>
<l>where the bull elephant with rising musth stands in front of [his] dark cow,</l>
<l>bends the young bamboo with big knots [and] offers [it to her],</l>
<l>	mixed with the honey that was nearby,</l>
<l>the mountain of the one with a mixed cloud colour.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
